the publisher and he says... No, in each case, I originated the concept of the

23:54.660 --> 24:09.560
anthology. If I was doing it in collaboration with somebody else, then the other
editor and I put this out on the market and a publisher who was interested would

24:09.560 --> 24:22.620
simply offer his contract. Did you ever meet John Campbell? Yes, I spent six
hours at his office. I think it was in 1970, just a year or so before his death.

24:22.620 --> 24:26.960
I don't remember the exact date. It was quite an experience.

